qElemNo.desc:
Rank number of the value.
If set to -1, it means that the value is not an element number.

qValue.desc:
Value of the cell.
Is set to NaN, if the value is not a number.

qCanExpand.desc:
If set to true, it means that the cell can be expanded.
This parameter isnot returned if it is set to false.

qCanCollapse.desc:
If set to true, it means that the cell can be collapsed.
This parameter isnot returned if it is set to false.

values.V: NX_DIM_CELL_VALUE. Applies to values in the data matrix.
values.E: NX_DIM_CELL_EMPTY. Applies to empty cells in the top and left dimensions.
values.N: NX_DIM_CELL_NORMAL. Applies to left and top dimensions cells.
values.T: NX_DIM_CELL_TOTAL. Applies to cells marked with Total
values.U: NX_DIM_CELL_NULL. Applies to Null values in the data matrix.

qMaxPos.desc: Total of the positive values in the current group of cells.

qMinNeg.desc: Total of the negative values in the current group of cells.

qUp.desc: Number of elements that are part of the previous tail.

qDown.desc: Number of elements that are part of the next tail.

qRow.desc:
Row index in the data matrix.
The indexing starts from 0.

qSubNodes.desc:
Information about sub nodes (or sub cells).
The array is empty [ ] when there is no sub nodes.
